[SN]TITLE[SN]
Matt Kilgallon: Bradford City sign former Sheff Utd and Blackburn defender

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
League One side Bradford City have signed former Blackburn Rovers defender Matt Kilgallon.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 32-year-old centre-back has agreed a one-year contract with the Bantams, with the option of a second year.
The former Leeds, Sheffield United and Sunderland player left Rovers earlier this summer after making 64 appearances during three years at Ewood Park.
"We're delighted to have brought in someone of Matt's pedigree," City boss Stuart McCall told the club website.
